  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in kadhai over medium heat.",
    "Add onion, garlic, carrot, celery, leeks, and red peppers. Sauté until softened.",
    "Stir in mustard and tomato paste, cooking for about a minute to allow the flavors to meld together.",
    "Pour in 200ml of water or vegetable stock. Bring to boil then reduce heat to low.",
    "Cover with a lid, place shaggy cheese on top of vegetables, cover again if necessary, and simmer gently for 30 minutes.",
    "Remove from heat once the mixture has thickened slightly. Let it rest for a few more minutes before serving."
